  "body": "Currently, Hyperledger Besu requires a series of additional processes to run side by side to it to report the health to ethnetstats servers.\n\n * Change to use an embedded process that reports health and information directly to ethnetstats servers over a web socket (not sure)\n * Use the same form of report as what geth uses, as an additional command line argument.\n * Optionally, allow the same command line argument parameter to be set as a config item.\n\n--- \n\nMigrated from the Besu Jira. Comment discussions from original issue: \n\n> @atoulme: I have opened a draft PR with a proposal here: https://github.com/hyperledger/besu/pull/383\n> @timbeiko: given that the PR for this is closed, do you think we should also close this issue?\n> @atoulme: No, I believe the need is still there. However, the PR was closed since a better approach leveraging the plugin API was offered.\n\n\n\n",
